@gjacoby126 Here is my understanding overall, please correct me if I'm wrong. There are 2 basic paths:

(Client-side delete and upsert-values) Client issues Puts/Deletes directly: This is handled in MutationState. annotateMutationsWithMetadata()
(Server-side delete and upsert-selects) Client issues scans, the server intercepts this and issues Put/Delete mutations based on the results read: This is what this method handles right? My understanding is we set the scan attributes in UpsertCompiler and DeleteCompiler and this is intercepted in UngroupedAggregateRegionScanner  where we read the scan attribute and set it on the mutations.

